<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-07-17T02:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-07-17T02:35:00-05:00" n="640" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d640">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">791.003/151: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Persia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Philip</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-07-17T11:00:00+03:25"><hi rend="italic">July 17,
                                        1928—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 12:45
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>73. Department’s mail instruction No. 621 of May 31.<note n="59" xml:id="d640fn59">See footnote 50, <ref target="#pg_737">p.
                                    737</ref>.</note> The treaty section of the Persian Foreign
                            Office objects to the refusal of the consulate at Teheran to issue a
                            nonimmigrant treaty-alien visa and claims a contravention of the
                            favored-nation stipulation in paragraph 2 of the provisional arrangement
                            dated May 14 between Persia and the United States.<note n="60" xml:id="d640fn60"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_724">pp. 724</ref>, <ref target="#pg_732">732</ref>.</note> Unless
                            the principle involved is clarified satisfactorily, difficulties may be
                            encountered in regard to other provisions of that agreement. Has the
                            Department any further instructions?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Philip</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>